<html>
<head>
    <style>
        .box {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: grey;
            margin: 50px;
        }

        .fixed {
            position: fixed;
            top: 80px;
            left: 80px;
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            background-color: red;
        }

        .newbox {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: grey;
            margin: 50px;
            transform: scale(1);
        }

        .newfixed {
            position: fixed;
            top: 10px;
            left: 10px;
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            background-color: red;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h4>This demo shows how 'transform' property change 'fixed' property's position.</h4>
    <p>'fixed' property is not realated with 'position:relative'</p>
    <div style="position:relative;">
        <div class="box">
            <div class="fixed"></div>
        </div>
        <br /><br /><br />
        <div class="newbox">
            <div class="newfixed"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>